sources.title: Unpublished Story
sources.description: “Better than you’d expect” “Worthwhile viewing” “Superior wartime drama” (IMDB reviews quotes) While working during the height of the London blitz two young newspaper reporters (Greene & Hobson) expose a hidden Nazi plot. Worthy all-British cast. Good production values for type. IMDB rating 6.4. Directed by Harold French. Released in 1942 (UK only) Complete print (PAL transfer). CAST NOTE: George Thorpe’s feature film debut.

metadata.Plot: A journalist investigates a network of German fifth columnists operating in the midst of the Blitz.
metadata.Writer: Anthony Havelock-Allan, Allan MacKinnon, Anatole de Grunwald
metadata.Actors: Richard Greene, Valerie Hobson, Basil Radford
